{"word":"συκοφαντέω","slug":"συκοφαντέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>συκοφαντέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:συκοφάντης'><el>συκοφάντης</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to accuse falsely, slander, calumniate</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be falsely accused</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to misrepresent</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>:—but also, <i>to extort by false accusations</i>, <b><a href='S:Lysias'>Lys.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to deal in false accusations</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>: generally, <i>to deal falsely, to give false counsel</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}